    "body": "We considered the idea of a single port per task, but I think that with typed messaging it is not a very good idea.  It is very common to have ports that are only used for a small set of messages, and there is no reason to pollute the general type of the task mailbox for that.\n\nAnyway, the `spawn_listener()` routine that @brson added fulfills the need of \"launch an actor with a single mailbox without a lot of fuss\":\n\n```\nspawn_listener {|port|\n    while true {\n        alt comm::recv(port) {\n               ....\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n",
